comments: Favors (NOP) establishes himself in a legal position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and gives him room to avoid contact.
Mitchell (UTA) makes makes marginal contact with Ingram's (NOP) arm at the end of his drive that does not affect his SQBR.
Ball (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Mitchell's (UTA) path and makes slight contact as they disengage.
Ingles (UTA) slightly turns his body against Jackson (NOP) contesting his driving shot attempt but contact is marginal.
Ingles (UTA) establishes himself in legal position in Ball's (NOP) path during the pick and absorbs the contact.
Favors (NOP) places his hand momentarily to Gobert's (UTA) side and slides his hand off.
Ball (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Mitchell (UTA).
Ingles (UTA) maintains legal position during Ingram's (NOP) drive and cleanly dislodges the ball at the end of his drive.
Hart (NOP) turns his body into Ingles' (UTA) as they engage for the loose ball and dislodges him from his position.
Ingram (NOP) briefly grasps O'Neale's (UTA) jersey during his drive and releases as his momentum is retreating.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact to Ingram's (NOP) wrist during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Favors (NOP) and Gobert (UTA) briefly engage and disengage while rebounding.
Ball (NOP) engage and disengage with Mitchell (UTA) prior to receiving the pass.
Hart (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of O'Neale (UTA) and makes slight contact as they disengage.
Favors (NOP) establishes himself in legal position in O'Neale's (UTA) path during the pick and gives him room to avoid contact.

During the inbound pass, multiple players engage to establish positions. Gobert (UTA) reaches forward and initiates contact with Hayes (NOP), who briefly takes his arm and lets go. There is a lot of contact among all of the players, with no single action that stands out as dislodging or impeding an opponent. Note this play was reviewed to confirm the timing of the foul with respect to the ball being released, not the foul itself.
Mitchell (UTA) makes marginal contact with Ingram's (NOP) front and side during his drive into the lane.
Jackson (NOP) moves alongside of Mitchell (UTA) and makes marginal contact to his front as he gathers the ball and begins his upward shooting motion.
Ingram (NOP) makes hand on ball contact on the play at the basket by Gobert (UTA).

The replay review of the foul called on Gobert (UTA) pursuant to coachs challenged was deemed unsuccessful because there was not conclusive evidence to overturn the call based on Gobert being late to the spot and turning when he makes contact with Ingram (NOP).
Bogdanovic (UTA) establishes himself in a legal position in Jackson's (NOP) path during the pick and makes slight contact as they disengage.
Bradley (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Jackson's (NOP) path and gives him room to avoid contact.
Moore (NOP) cleanly deflects the pass by Bogdanovic (UTA).
Moore (NOP) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes three steps after the gather.
Jackson (NOP) and Mitchell (UTA) engage and disengage off ball.
Mitchell (UTA) makes contact to Moore's (NOP) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bradley (UTA) hops on the same foot consecutively after gathering the ball.
Favors (NOP) places a collapsing arm against Bradley's (UTA) side at the top of trajectory and does not extend.
Favors (NOP) establishes himself in legal position in O'Neale's (UTA) path during the pick and absorbs the contact.
Bradley (UTA) makes contact to Ingram's (NOP) body during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.

Jackson (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Mitchell (NOP) during his drive.  As Mitchell regains control of the loose ball Jackson momentary places two hand against Mitchell's body and slides it off.
Bogdanovic (UTA) engage and disengage with Ball (NOP) after he makes his pass.
O'Neale (UTA) commits a take foul on Ingram (NOP).
Bradley (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Jackson (NOP) and abosrbs the contact.
Mitchell (UTA) grabs Jackson's (NOP) arm during the rebound that affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
